<title>ITALY: Italy's Milan sees Jan CPI at 0.2 pct mo/mo.</title>
<headline>Italy's Milan sees Jan CPI at 0.2 pct mo/mo.</headline>
<dateline>MILAN 1997-01-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Milan said its January consumer price index stood at 0.2 percent month-on-month and 2.8 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In December, Milan's inflation rate was 0.1 percent and 2.7 percent respectively.</p>
<p>Milan is one of 11 Italian cities to publish inflation data on Monday and Tuesday.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 19.1 percent on the national index. The 11 sample cities have a combined weighting of 75.66 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to December 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.2   (0.1)     2.8  (2.7)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.2   (0.0)     2.2  (3.0)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.1   (0.4)     3.9  (3.7)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   1.9   (0.1)     9.4  (9.1)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.0   (0.0)     2.4  (2.4)</p>
<p>    Health services		   2.1   (0.0)     3.3  (2.2)</p>
<p>    Transportation		   -0.7   (0.1)     0.8 (-0.9)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture    -0.7   (0.6)     0.8  (1.7)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.0   (0.0)     4.1  (2.6)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.9   (0.1)     3.7  (3.7)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	 0.0   (0.0)     1.4  (1.8)</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom +392 66129526</p>
